LEX The Door.

"First Person" is a person.
"Keystone" is a person.
"Fold" is a text.
"Door Opened" is a binary.

The First Person appoints the Keystone, and fixes the Fold.

CLAUSE: Present.
The Keystone may send the Fold to the First Person.

CLAUSE: Open.
The First Person may declare Door Opened.

CLAUSE: Push.
The First Person may, if Door Opened is declared: register the Fold.
